summaries.short: Bethenny confronts a source of drama and gets ready for a difficult elimination – but struggles to showcase her trademark decisiveness. Just as the final four candidates get comfortable, they face an unnerving curveball.
summaries.full: While the photoshoot challenge continues, Bethenny confronts a source of drama – and struggles to tell a friendly face that they’ve bungled a crucial task. After meeting the group back at the loft to evaluate their shots, Bethenny struggles to showcase her trademark decisiveness at elimination. Later, the candidates prepare themselves for a massive curveball.

summaries.short: Tasked with preparing Bethenny for a televised sales appearance, the contestants brace themselves for an unnerving twist: they’ll have to sell the products themselves – on live TV.
summaries.full: What begins as a straightforward project – preparing Bethenny for a Skinnygirl clothing sales appearance – turns into the contestants’ highest-stakes undertaking yet when Bethenny announces they’ll have to sell the products themselves … on live TV.

summaries.short: Putting the group’s marketing and time management skills to the test with a photoshoot challenge for her bestselling shapewear, Bethenny finds herself pleasantly surprised by some – and taken aback by the ineptitude of others.
summaries.full: After introducing the remaining contestants to their new workspace, a stunning Soho loft, Bethenny reminds them that this is the interview of a lifetime – and they better start acting the part. Giving the first challenge’s winner a special edge – and emphasizing that effective time management should be their first priority – Bethenny spurs the group to produce an ad campaign for her inclusive, bestselling shapewear line. But when faced with criticism, some can’t handle the heat.

summaries.short: As the competitors are paired off to produce a video campaign for BStrong, Bethenny’s disaster relief initiative, who will impress the boss with their execution, and who will crumble in the face of chaos?
summaries.full: After throwing two colossal curveballs, Bethenny directs the group to produce a video campaign for BStrong, a disaster relief initiative close to her heart. Paired off for the first time, duos must work together to crystallize and convey a concise, poignant message for Bethenny’s website – but when chaos strikes, will they impress the boss with their calm execution, or will they fall apart?

summaries.short: Bethenny kicks off the search for her VP of Operations with a cocktail party, where first impressions send candidates home before they can say “Skinnygirl.” Later, a social media aptitude test leaves Bethenny underwhelmed.
summaries.full: As she looks to hire a well-rounded, razor-sharp second-in-command, business mogul Bethenny Frankel welcomes ten hopeful candidates to the competition with a swank cocktail party. Scanning the room for a potential VP of Operations, Bethenny plants two moles to gather intel, and later, a social media aptitude test leaves her underwhelmed for the first elimination round.
